In the above, the value formula_12 is a free parameter, usually taken to be real such that formula_95 (but can be complex in general), and so the elliptic functions can be thought of as being given by two variables, formula_11 and the parameter formula_12. The remaining nine elliptic functions are easily built from the above three (formula_1, formula_99, formula_100), and are given in a section below. Note that when formula_101, that formula_11 then equals the quarter period formula_37.

In the most general setting, formula_104 is a multivalued function (in formula_11) with infinitely many logarithmic branch points (the branches differ by integer multiples of formula_106), namely the points formula_107 and formula_108 where formula_109. This multivalued function can be made single-valued by cutting the complex plane along the line segments joining these branch points (the cutting can be done in non-equivalent ways, giving non-equivalent single-valued functions), thus making formula_104 analytic everywhere except on the branch cuts. In contrast, formula_111 and other elliptic functions have no branch points, give consistent values for every branch of formula_112, and are meromorphic in the whole complex plane. Since every elliptic function is meromorphic in the whole complex plane (by definition), formula_104 (when considered as a single-valued function) is not an elliptic function.

However, a particular cutting for formula_104 can be made in the formula_11-plane by line segments from formula_116 to formula_108 with formula_109; then it only remains to define formula_104 at the branch cuts by continuity from some direction. Then formula_104 becomes single-valued and singly-periodic in formula_11 with the minimal period formula_122 and it has singularities at the logarithmic branch points mentioned above. If formula_123 and formula_124, formula_104 is continuous in formula_11 on the real line. When formula_127, the branch cuts of formula_104 in the formula_11-plane cross the real line at formula_130 for formula_131; therefore for formula_127, formula_104 is not continuous in formula_11 on the real line and jumps by formula_106 on the discontinuities.

But defining formula_104 this way gives rise to very complicated branch cuts in the formula_12-plane (&quot;not&quot; the formula_11-plane); they have not been fully described as of yet.

