* Hurricane Irma (2017) – A destructive Category 5 hurricane that took a similar track
* Hurricane Dorian (2019) – Another Category 5 hurricane of an almost identical intensity that made landfall in the Bahamas on U.S. Labor Day
* Hurricane Ian (2022) – A devastating and destructive Category 5 Hurricane that is the deadliest hurricane to make landfall in Florida since this hurricane
